We are excited about the great things to come throughout this new school year, as we continue to serve our growing school community!

post_text:
Thank you, Ms Cuevas. We love hearing about the success our students and families are having at OCVA!

OVCA is by far the best school my son has ever had the privilege of attending. Over the years, not only has his attitude about education improved, but he has had outstanding grades, as well as being on the Honor Roll a couple of times. The school's teachers are always there for the students, no matter what the kids' questions and concerns are, To me, this is what school should be all about. I highly recommend OVCA for anyone who is dealing with brick and mortar schools.

Children express and receive love in different ways - some through acts of service, others through affirming words, and still others through gifts, quality time, or physical touch. Each of these expressions of love represents a different "language." Based on the book The Five Love Languages by Gary Chapman, Dr. Boyd will explain and discuss each of the love languages and provide strategies that enable parents to speak to their children's love language.

Join us this Wednesday (10/30) at 8:00pm EST to learn more on this important topic! Check out the Announcements section in OLS for details and to register.
